hopobject.body: I'm on business can prednisone cause costochondritis NASA estimates suggest InSight should have a 99 percent chance of landing within its chosen ellipse if the mission targets the ellipse's center. Mission scientists also considered portions of Valles Marineris, the famed "Grand Canyon of Mars," and a region dubbed Isidis Planitia for the InSight landing, but those areas were ultimately considered too rocky, windy or uneven to ensure a successful landing.
